label: anatomical structure
definition: Structure components within a metazoan organism; body part.

label: cell
definition: A material entity that has a plasma membrane and results from cellular division.

label: anatomical region
definition: Structural regions within a metazoan organism.
comment: UBERON has different label: organism subdivision

label: pelvis
comment: UBERON has different label: pelvic region of trunk

label: whisker
comment: UBERON has different label: strand of vibrissa hair

label: lateral
definition: Structural region referring to the side of a metazoan organism's body or body part.
editors note: This might be worth adding to UBERON perhaps as subclass to organism subdivision

label: red blood cell
comment: CL has a different label: erythrocyte

label: packed red blood cells
definition: Red blood cells that have been separated for blood transfusion.
editors note: Could be added to an appropriated OBO ontology see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Packed_red_blood_cells.
